commit.message: Back to development: 0.2.1
Preparing release 0.2.0

CHANGES entries and bump version

Note the simplified implementation using newer support from buildout,
the dropping of `humpty` as dependency, and the `.ovo` dist directories
in `eggs-directory`.

Merge pull request #9 from buildout/humpty-had-a-great-fall

Humpty had a great fall
Use released zc.buildout
Use `.ovo` as the non-egg dist extension.

Look, Ma! No Buildout subclasses either!

After further refactoring of the Buildout API itself, now we can just
add a, say, wheel unpacker to the "registry" of distribution
unpacking functions, instead of subclassing `easy_install.Installer`.

Look, Ma! No foreign subclasses!

Stop subclassing `pkg_resources.Environment`.

Just override `Installer._call_easy_install()` to unpack wheels
inside `eggs-directory` such that `Installer` knows to find them.

Use a WheelFile adapter instead of subclass

Using composition, instead of inheritance, replace the WheelFile subclass
with a WheelFile adapter.

Helps reducing the code of the `distros_for_location()` monkeypatch

Look, Ma! no wheel_to_egg!

Handle the wheel conversion inside Installer._call_easy_install

This means we don't need to delay tempdirs cleanup.

Replace `.whl` with `.dist` for wheel directories

They're not just unzipped wheels. File have been moved around, so
we should not reuse the extension.

Instead, let's call them just `dist`.

Also, feed everything in `eggs-directory`  that can be a dist to
`Environment`, both .egg and .dist entries.

Finally, move the tempdir cleanup handling to `wheel_to_egg` and the
extension unloading to get rid of `SelfDestructingDistro`.

Forget laying eggs from wheels: use the wheels

Unpack wheels directly as directories inside `eggs-directory`

Override `zc.buildout.easy_install.Installer` to feed the wheels inside
`eggs-directory` to `pkg_resources.Environment`.

That's enough for `pkg_resources` to read all the metadata.

Too bad... I liked the `lay_egg_into()` method name...

Safer egg laying.

Avoid creating (and destroying) the egg in the download cache to
begin with.

Do it in a tempdir inside the download cache instead and destroy the
tmpdir afterwards.

Attempt to replace humpty

Things that work:

 * installation
 * entry points
 * scripts w/ or w/o entry points
 * namespace packages

Things that don't:

 * dependencies/requirements

More surgical monkey-patch into setuptools

Patch only `distros_for_location` instead of both
`interpret_distro_name` and `EXTENSIONS`

TMP: tweak travis to use the zc.buildout branch we depend on.

Please drop this commit before merging.
